  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "In a bowl, mix together chickpeas, coconut oil, garlic, Thai red chili, fish sauce, and palm sugar (if using).",
    "Spread the mixture on a baking sheet and roast in the oven for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "In a pan, heat a tablespoon of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the fried shallots and cook until fragrant.",
    "Add the toasted rice, lemongrass, and chili powder (if using) to the pan and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the roasted chickpeas to the pan and stir to combine.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the chickpeas over fry-grind-rice-khao-khua.",
    "Garnish with additional fried shallots and toasted rice if desired."
  ],
